modules.description: Provides functions to generate JavaScript code from OCaml modules, including symbol mapping and type conversion. Operates on OCaml abstract syntax trees and JavaScript ASTs. Used to embed OCaml code in web applications by translating module interfaces and values into compatible JavaScript representations.

Provides functions to integrate js_of_ocaml compilation into ocamlbuild, handling executable conversion and target mapping. Operates on pathname lists and ocamlbuild hooks to generate JavaScript outputs from OCaml bytecodes. Enables building standalone JavaScript files from specific executables during the build process.
